  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Category:</strong> Clan<br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Claymore Clan, Level 8+<br />Your swordplay is particularly polished, even for someone of your calibur. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li>While you are wearing light or medium armor you gain a +1d4 bonus to martial arts checks and any contested martial arts checks are made at advantage.</li><li>Your Claymore gains an additional weapon group that is not thrown or ammunition and gains an additional rank of a property it already has or gains the critical, disarm, tactical, or trip property.</li><li>When you would force a creature to make multiple saving throws as a result of a Claymore clan hijutsu or feature in the same action you can instead force them to make only one saving throw of your choice, as long as it would be a saving throw that they would have to make. If they fail this saving throw they suffer all of the effects.</li></ul>",
